<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>

<exercises xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="exer-consistency" ><title>Additional Practice</title>
<exercisegroup cols="2">
  <introduction>
  <p>
    In the following exercises, find the solution to the given linear system.
    If the system has infinite solutions,
    give <m>2</m> particular solutions.
  </p>
  </introduction>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow>2x_1 + 4x_2\amp = 2</mrow>
          <mrow> x_1 +  2x_2\amp = 1 </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=1-2x_2</m>; <m>x_2</m> is free.
        Two possible particular solutions: <m>x_1=1</m>,
        <m>x_2=0</m> or <m>x_1=-1</m>, <m>x_2=1</m>.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow> -x_1 + 5x_2\amp = 3</mrow>
          <mrow> 2x_1 - 10x_2\amp = -6 </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=-3+5x_2</m>; <m>x_2</m> is free.
        Two possible particular solutions: <m>x_1 = 3</m>,
        <m>x_2=0</m> or <m>x_1 = -8</m>, <m>x_2 = -1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow> x_1 + x_2\amp = 3</mrow> 
          <mrow> 2x_1 + x_2\amp = 4 </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=1</m>; <m>x_2=2</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow>-3x_1 + 7x_2\amp = -7</mrow>
          <mrow> 2x_1 - 8x_2\amp = 8 </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=0</m>; <m>x_2=-1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow>2x_1 + 3x_2\amp = 1</mrow>
          <mrow> -2x_1 - 3x_2\amp = 1 </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        No solution; the system is inconsistent.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow> x_1+ 2x_2\amp = 1</mrow>
          <mrow> -x_1- 2x_2\amp = 5 </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        No solution; the system is inconsistent.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow> -2x_1+ 4x_2+ 4x_3\amp = 6</mrow>
          <mrow> x_1- 3x_2+ 2x_3\amp = 1 </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=-11+10x_3</m>; <m>x_2=-4+4x_3</m>; <m>x_3</m> is free.
        Two possible particular solutions: <m>x_1=-11</m>, <m>x_2 = -4</m>,
        <m>x_3=0</m> or <m>x_1 = -1</m>,
        <m>x_2 = 0</m> and <m>x_3 = 1</m>.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow> -x_1+ 2x_2+ 2x_3\amp = 2</mrow> 
          <mrow> 2x_1+ 5x_2+ x_3\amp = 2 </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=-\frac23+\frac89x_3</m>;
        <m>x_2=\frac23-\frac59x_3</m>; <m>x_3</m> is free.
        Two possible particular solutions: <m>x_1 = -\frac23</m>, <m>x_2 = \frac23</m>,
        <m>x_3 = 0</m> and <m>x_1 = \frac49</m>,
        <m>x_2 = -\frac19</m>, <m>x_3 = 1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow>-x_1-x_2+x_3+x_4\amp = 0</mrow>
          <mrow> -2x_1-2x_2+x_3\amp = -1 </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=1-x_2-x_4</m>; <m>x_2</m> is free;
        <m>x_3=1-2x_4</m>; <m>x_4</m> is free.
        Two possible solutions: <m>x_1 = 1</m>,
        <m>x_2 = 0</m>, <m>x_3 = 1</m>,
        <m>x_4 = 0</m> or <m>x_1 = -2</m>, <m>x_2 = 1</m>,
        <m>x_3 = -3</m>, <m>x_4=2</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow> x_1+x_2+6x_3+9x_4\amp = 0</mrow>
          <mrow> -x_1-x_3-2x_4\amp = -3 </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=3-x_3-2x_4</m>; <m>x_2=-3-5x_3-7x_4</m>;
        <m>x_3</m> is free; <m>x_4</m> is free.
        Two possible solutions: <m>x_1 =3</m>,
        <m>x_2 = -3</m>, <m>x_3=0</m>,
        <m>x_4=0</m> or <m>x_1 = 0</m>,
        <m>x_2 = -5</m>, <m>x_3 =-1</m>, <m>x_4=1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow> 2x_1+ x_2+ 2x_3\amp = 0</mrow>
          <mrow> x_1+ x_2+ 3x_3\amp = 1</mrow>
          <mrow> 3x_1+ 2x_2+ 5x_3\amp = 3 </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        No solution; the system is inconsistent.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow> x_1+ 3x_2+ 3x_3\amp = 1</mrow>
          <mrow> 2x_1- x_2+ 2x_3\amp = -1</mrow>
          <mrow> 4x_1+ 5x_2+ 8x_3\amp = 2 </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        No solution; the system is inconsistent.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow> x_1+ 2x_2+ 2x_3\amp =1</mrow>
          <mrow> 2x_1+ x_2+ 3x_3\amp = 1</mrow>
          <mrow> 3x_1+ 3x_2+ 5x_3\amp = 2 </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=\frac13-\frac43x_3</m>;
        <m>x_2=\frac13-\frac13x_3</m>; <m>x_3</m> is free.
        Two possible solutions: <m>x_1 = \frac13</m>, <m>x_2=\frac13</m>,
        <m>x_3=0</m> or <m>x_1 = -1</m>,
        <m>x_2 = 0</m>, <m>x_3=1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow> 2x_1+ 4x_2+ 6x_3\amp = 2</mrow>
          <mrow> 1x_1+ 2x_2+ 3x_3\amp = 1</mrow>
          <mrow> -3x_1- 6x_2- 9x_3\amp = -3 </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x_1=1-2x_2-3x_3</m>; <m>x_2</m> is free; <m>x_3</m> is free.
        Two possible solutions: <m>x_1=1</m>, <m>x_2=0</m>,
        <m>x_3=0</m> or <m>x_1=8</m>,
        <m>x_2=1</m>, <m>x_3 = -3</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
 </exercisegroup>
 <exercisegroup cols="2">
  <introduction>
  <p>
    In the following exercises,
    state for which values of <m>k</m> the given system will have exactly <m>1</m> solution,
    infinite solutions, or no solution.
  </p>
  </introduction>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow> x_1+ 2x_2\amp = 1</mrow>
          <mrow>2x_1+ 4x_2\amp = k </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        Never exactly <m>1</m> solution; infinite solutions if <m>k=2</m>;
        no solution if <m>k\neq 2</m>.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow>x_1+ 2x_2\amp = 1</mrow>
          <mrow>x_1+ kx_2\amp = 1 </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        Exactly <m>1</m> solution if <m>k\neq 2</m>;
        infinite solutions if <m>k=2</m>; never no solution.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow>x_1+ 2x_2\amp = 1</mrow>
          <mrow> x_1+ kx_2\amp = 2 </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        Exactly <m>1</m> solution if <m>k\neq 2</m>;
        no solution if <m>k=2</m>;
        never infinite solutions.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        <md>
          <mrow>x_1+ 2x_2\amp = 1</mrow>
          <mrow> x_1+ 3x_2\amp = k </mrow>
        </md>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        Exactly <m>1</m> solution for all <m>k</m>.
      </p>
    </answer>
  </exercise>
 </exercisegroup>
    
</exercises>